article.description: Mandy Morales scored 23 points as Montana claimed the Big Sky Conference tournament championship with a 69-62 win over Portland State.
article.headline: Morales, Ena lead way as Montana wins Big Sky final
article.linkText: Montana edges Portland St. for Big Sky crown
article.story:
MISSOULA, Mont. -- Big Sky MVP Mandy Morales had 23 points and nine rebounds and Sarah Ena added 19 points and 14 rebounds Saturday as Montana claimed the league tournament championship with a 69-62 win over Portland State.

Montana (28-4), which also won the regular-season title, earned the league's automatic berth in the NCAA tournament.

The Lady Griz pulled away from Portland State (22-9) after a 3-pointer by Claire Faucher gave the Vikings a 48-47 lead with 6:08 remaining.

Two free throws by Ena with 5:04 remaining gave Montana the lead for good and started a 17-of-20 run from the free throw line for the Lady Griz.

Montana led by as much as 58-50 on two free throws by Lauren Beck with 2:42 remaining. Portland State got no closer than 59-55 on a 3-pointer by Faucher with 1:29 to play.

Sonja Rogers added 12 points for the Lady Griz, who advanced to the NCAA tournament for the 18th time in school history. Montana's 28 wins matches a school record set by the 1987-88 team.

Faucher led Portland State (22-9) with 17 points and five rebounds while Kelli Valentine had 16 points.

Montana led 27-26 at halftime.
